>I'd use 20A circuit breakers available at your FLAPS.  They connect with
>spade terminals and should be placed back near the starter end of the
>wires.  Otherwise use 20A AGC fuses in an in-line holder.  Get a well-made
>holder, one that grips the fuse and is not just spring-loaded.  Good ones
>come from Japanese cars and motorcycles or Radio Shack.

If there is one fuse per relay per headlight, why 20A?  A 55W bulb is drawing less than 5A at 12V.

